    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-02-22T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-02-22T11:00:00-05:00" n="24"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d24">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15a3/704a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chairman of the American Delegation</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stimson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-02-22T11:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 22, 1930—11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>131. Being somewhat disturbed, we desire that your feeling about the Conference
                    be made known to us more fully. There is undoubtedly a waning of public interest
                    here. While this may be inevitable and perhaps should not bother us, there is a
                    strong feeling here that nothing is being done to keep down the levels which in
                    every category being considered by the Conference are terribly high. I regret to
                    have to bother you, but more frequent reports are needed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cotton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
